defaultWhile local authorities now commission 
defaultmost 
defaultpublic health services, there is still a role in this for the NHS. 
defaultSignificant initiatives led by both NHS providers and commissioners have strengthened early intervention efforts in areas such as psychiatric liaison, alcohol and falls prevention. However, our members have clearly stated this sort of work has often been driven by certain individuals and it is not yet something built into the NHS system. We must ensure these initiatives become the norm across the health service.
