default5.defaultThe interaction between mental health conditions and long-term physical health conditionsdefault&#xa0;
default5.1 People with long-term physical health conditions will often have psychological and 
defaultemotional needs resulting from
default 
defaultillness-related symptoms, 
defaultdisability
default associated with the physical illness, 
defaultor
default the impact of living with more than one physical condition at any time. 
defaultFor example, d
defaultepression is at least twice as common in people with diabetes, with an estimated 41 per cent of people with diabetes having poor psychological wellbeing, and many with
default 
defaultpsychological needs that do not meet the criteria for a formal diagnosis. Evidence shows that depression exacerbates the complications and adverse consequences of diabetes,
default 
defaultin part because patients 
defaulthave difficulties with 
defaultmanage their diabetes. 
default&#xa0;
default5.2 The NHS therefore needs to ensure that services are designed and delivered around the needs of an individual as a whole. It is important the mental health and the re
defaultst of the system work in a joined 
defaultup way, particularly in developing and delivering integrated care for people with long term conditions. 
