default5
default.3
default 
defaultFailing to recognise the link has
default economic costs - 
defaulth
defaultealthcare costs are higher and productivity is lower due to reduced work performance, increased absenteeism and withdrawal from the labour force. 
defaultFor example, i
defaultn the UK, individuals with co-morbid depression and diabetes are four times more likely to have difficulties in self-managing their health and seven times more likely to have days off work
default compared to people with diabetes alone
default.
default 
defaultEvidence shows
default that a
defaultddressing psychological needs
default of diabetic people through a range of interventions such as cognitive behavioural therapy (CBT) or anti-depressant therapy include: reduced psychological distress and anxiety; improved mood and quality of life; improved relationships with health professionals and significant others; and improved eating-related b
defaultehaviours such as purging 
defaultand body image symptoms
